{"id":"shadow","term":"Shadow","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Used in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Colossians 2:17\">Col. 2:17</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 8:5\">Heb. 8:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 10:1\">10:1</a> to denote the typical relation of the Jewish to the Christian dispensation.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Colossians 2:17","Hebrews 8:5","Hebrews 10:1"]}